import java.util.Base64;
import java.util.Base64.Encoder;

String base64Password = Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString("emailPassword".getBytes());
System.out.println(base64Password);
```

Replace "email" with your email account's username or domain name. The code uses the Base64 encoding format to encode the password into a string and then prints it out to the console. You can then use this string as the password for your email account.

